"```sql\nSELECT \n    (COUNT(*) * 100.0 / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM superhero)) AS percentage_of_self_interested_superheroes,\n    COUNT(CASE WHEN publisher.publisher_name = 'Marvel Comics' THEN 1 END) AS marvel_self_interested_superheroes\nFROM \n    superhero\nJOIN \n    alignment ON superhero.alignment_id = alignment.id\nJOIN \n    publisher ON superhero.publisher_id = publisher.id\nWHERE \n    alignment.alignment = 'Neutral';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of superheroes who act in their own self-interest or make decisions based on their own moral code (which corresponds to the 'Neutral' alignment based on the schema description) and counts how many of these superheroes were published by Marvel Comics. The query uses a JOIN operation to connect the `superhero`, `alignment`, and `publisher` tables based on their foreign key relationships."